## Summary

I attempted to remove PROJECT-2887 from the Epic PROJECT-1066 by modifying the parent issue, but both attempts failed:

1. Attempt 1: Used {"update": {"Epic Child": [{"remove": {"key": "PROJECT-2887"}}]}} - The update appeared successful but PROJECT-2887 still remains as a child of PROJECT-1066.

2. Attempt 2: Tried a different field approach but got an error calling the update_issue tool.

Conclusion: The MCP Atlassian integration appears to have limitations in properly handling Epic-Child relationship removal. The approach of modifying the parent Epic to remove
children doesn't seem to work reliably through the MCP tools.

The most reliable method remains using the jira-cli command line tool as we tried earlier, which showed success in the CLI output even though the API responses may still show cached relationships.
```
